This article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama declaring Thursday, November 28, 2013, as a National Day of Thanksgiving. Obama emphasizes the importance of Thanksgiving as a time to count our blessings, spend time with loved ones, and honor those who defend the nation. He mentions the historical roots of Thanksgiving and the values it represents. Obama also acknowledges the service of those serving the nation abroad, as well as first responders, medical professionals, and volunteers. He encourages people to forge deeper connections with loved ones, extend gratitude and compassion, and recognize that the nation rises or falls as one. Obama concludes by urging the people of the United States to join together in giving thanks, expressing appreciation, and sharing their bounty with others.